FBIS3-34400 "drnes026_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 LEBANON Possible Ties to Abu-Nidal Group Noted JN0702194594 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1900 GMT 7 Feb 94 JN0702194594 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] In Amman, a diplomatic source has announced that the Lebanese police have arrested two persons suspected of killing Na'ib al-Ma'ayitah, the Jordanian counselor at the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut who was assassinated in 29 January in the Lebanese capital. The same source added that the two arrested persons are Palestinians who belong to a hard-line group which could be Fatah-the Revolutionary Council led by Abu-Nidal.
